name: Caramelized Chicken Wings
author: Shannon Patrick Koller
summary: Yummy chicken wings that are so easy to fix on the stove top or in an electric skillet.
ingredients: 12  large chicken wings, tips removed and wings cut in half at joint
1 teaspoon sesame seeds, or to taste  (Optional)
directions: In an electric skillet or a large skillet over medium heat, mix together the water, sugar, soy sauce, peanut butter, honey, wine vinegar, and garlic until smooth and the sugar has dissolved
Place the wings into the sauce, cover, and simmer for 30 minutes
Uncover and simmer until the wings are tender and the sauce has thickened, about 30 more minutes, spooning sauce over wings occasionally
